THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

bayestruth has ZERO required runtime dependencies. Its core is node-free; the
audit seal uses the Web Crypto API, not node:crypto. The @takk sibling
packages are OPTIONAL peer dependencies, resolved only when you compose with
them, and each is distributed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

The core package pulls in none of the above. Only the @takk/bayestruth/node
entry point uses the Node standard library (node:fs) for durable persistence.

